Leaderboard Position: 497/402/395

Hello all! This is the second quest, which consists of doing operations with complex numbers and seeing if they diverge if running the given formula. In part 1, we are given a basic overview of complex numbers and how to do operations with them. For example, if we are given a complex number z, we run the formula...

```
z = (z^2 / b) + a

where z, b, a are complex numbers
```

If this isn't familiar to you, this is a modified version of a fractal calculations, specifically the [Mandelbrot set](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandelbrot_set). For this part, we are only doing 3 iterations and seeing what the result would be for our input. In part 2, we are seeing if the point we are given on a grid with go off past a limit or will stay within the bounds. If so, we "engrave" the point. For now, we are only doing every other 10 points, which means we only check `101*101=10201` points. In part 3, we are doing the same thing, except we are checking if every point in the grid will diverge or not. Here are the fractals that I generated below...
